Low-Memory RNA-Seq Pipeline

A lightweight, end-to-end RNA-Seq analysis pipeline optimized for low-memory machines (<8GB RAM). This bash script performs:

Streaming SRA download and conversion to FASTQ using fasterq-dump
Quality control with FastQC
Read alignment to GRCh38 using HISAT2
Gene-level read counting with featureCounts
Merging counts into a single matrix with Python
Differential expression analysis and KEGG pathway enrichment with Python (scipy + gseapy)

The pipeline is fully automated, handles reference genome download and indexing, and avoids storing large intermediate files to save memory.

Output:

Aligned BAM files (aligned/)
Gene counts per sample (counts/)
Merged count matrix (counts/counts_merged.txt)
Differentially expressed genes (DEG_results.csv)
KEGG enrichment results (KEGG_results/)

Designed for quick deployment on low-resource systems without sacrificing standard RNA-Seq workflow steps.
